	<h1>jQuery Socialist</h1>
	<h6>Create a single social media stream from multiple social networks</h6>
</div>

<p>
jQuery Socialist is a jquery plugin that creates a social stream (or social "wall") from multiple social media feeds in one place.
Use it to pull content from Facebook pages, Twitter, LinkedIn, YouTube and other social networks...
</p>

<div class="well">
	<h3>Features</h3>
	<ul>
    <li>Aggregates social feeds from <a href='#facebook'>Facebook</a>, <a href='#twitter'>Twitter</a>, LinkedIn, YouTube, Tumblr, Pinterest, RSS Feeds, Craigslist, Google+ and more..</li>
    <li>Multiple themes and responsive style</li>
    <li>Easy to implement with <A href='http://jquery.com'>jQuery</a> and a few lines of code!</li>
	</ul>
	<h3 title="Use it on your Website or Blog to...">Use Cases</h3>
	<ul>
	<li><a href=''>Show updates from multiple social networks in attractive visual layouts</a></li>
	<li><a href=''>Display Instagram photos in Pinterest-style layouts</a></li>
    <li><a href=''>Combine and display Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn updates</a></li>
    <li><a href=''>Show YouTube video thumbnails</a></li>
    <li><a href=''>Display Craiglist postings for an area and/or category</a></li>
    <li><a href=''>Visualize any RSS feed as a responsive social wall</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>
	
